    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - TACHOMETER - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <para>The electronic tachometer system consists of a dash unit, the sensor unit and the circuits in the wiring
            harness connecting the two units. The dash unit includes the tachometer head, which is an air core gauge,
            and the controlling circuits in the microprocessor. The sensor is mounted in the engine flywheel housing.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
